**MrBeast-Inspired Retention Principles**

-   **First minute is critical:** You win or lose most viewers here.
    Pre-plan it. Match your thumbnail promise immediately.

-   **Minutes 1-3 (Transition):** Stop telling people what they will be
    watching and start showing them.

-   **3-Minute re-engagement:** Include a \"spectacle\"---something
    impressive that only you can do.

-   **Back half content:** Once someone has watched 6 minutes, they\'re
    \"super invested.\" Longer explanations are acceptable here.

-   **Never signal the end:** Unless building to the payoff.

**PART 3**

**TEMPLATES & TOOLS**

**3.1 Script Notes Template System**

Script notes are sentence starters you glance at while recording.
They\'re not full scripts---just prompts to remind you what points to
hit. You finish each sentence naturally on camera, keeping your
authentic voice.

**Why It Works:**

-   Keeps your delivery natural (not memorized/robotic)

-   Ensures you hit all key points without forgetting

-   Easy to glance at while screen recording

-   Preserves your \"discovery energy\" voice

**How to Write Script Notes**

1.  **Start with the outcome.** What does the viewer walk away knowing?
    Write that first, then work backward.

2.  **Write sentence starters, not full sentences.** Each bullet is 3-6
    words that trigger the rest of the thought. You\'ll complete it
    naturally on camera.

3.  **Use ellipsis to signal continuation.** End each starter with
    \"\...\" so your brain knows to keep going.

4.  **Group by section with clear headers.** Bold section headers (HOOK,
    VALUE STACK, DEMO, CLOSE) so you can quickly find your place.

5.  **Keep it to one page.** If you can\'t see everything at once,
    you\'ll lose your place. Trim until it fits.

**Example Format**

**HOOK**

> ‚Ä¢ \[Result or bold claim\]\...
>
> ‚Ä¢ \[What this is\]\...

**VALUE STACK**

> ‚Ä¢ I use \[tool\] and\...
>
> ‚Ä¢ No \[pain point\]\...

**DEMO**

> ‚Ä¢ \[First action\]\...
>
> ‚Ä¢ Let\'s see if\...

**CLOSE**

> ‚Ä¢ \[Action CTA: try it, download, check it out\]\...

