**3.3 GifGrep Skill --- Finding Memes & GIFs**

Use gifgrep to search GIF providers (Tenor/Giphy), download results, and
extract stills for use in Fireship-style content. This tool makes
finding reaction GIFs fast and scriptable.

**Quick Start Examples**

\# Search for GIFs and get URLs

gifgrep \"mind blown\" \--max 5 \--format url

\# Download a GIF directly

gifgrep \"celebration\" \--download \--max 1

\# Extract a still frame (for thumbnails)

gifgrep still ./clip.gif \--at 1.5s -o still.png

\# Create a contact sheet (grid of frames)

gifgrep sheet ./clip.gif \--frames 9 \--cols 3 -o sheet.png

**Common Workflows for Content Creation**

**Finding Reaction GIFs for Videos:**

gifgrep \"shocked\" \--max 10 \--format url gifgrep \"this is fine\"
\--max 5 gifgrep \"thumbs up\" \--download \--max 1

**Key Options:**

  ----------------- -----------------------------------------------------
  **Option**        **Description**

  \--max N          Limit number of results

  \--format url     Output only URLs (pipe-friendly)

  \--json           Output full JSON with metadata

  \--download       Save GIF to \~/Downloads

  \--source         Choose provider: auto \| tenor \| giphy
  ----------------- -----------------------------------------------------

**Integration with Fireship-Style Videos:**

Remember: Fireship uses a meme/GIF every 20-30 seconds. Build a library
of common reactions:

-   \"mind blown\" --- for impressive features

-   \"this is fine\" --- for bugs/disasters

-   \"confused math\" --- for complex concepts

-   \"celebration\" --- for successful demos

-   \"surprised pikachu\" --- for obvious outcomes

