**4.3 The 7 Scripting Rules**

6.  **Lead with a claim, not context.** \"This is trending with 20K
    stars\" beats \"Let me show you this tool.\" Make the viewer curious
    about the claim before explaining it.

7.  **Never start with \"so,\" \"hey,\" or \"what\'s up.\"** These slow
    starts kill retention. Jump directly into value.

8.  **Name the tool in the first 5 seconds.** 40% of your top performers
    do this vs 25% of bottom. Specificity signals value immediately.

9.  **Use comparisons for credibility.** \"better than GPT-4\" appears
    in 18% of top videos vs 8% of bottom. Comparisons create instant
    context.

10. **Cut the filler words.** Your top videos have 14% fewer fillers
    (\"like,\" \"basically,\" \"you know\"). Script tightly.

11. **Don\'t ask---claim.** Question hooks have a 29% success rate. Bold
    claims have 80%. Make statements, not questions.

12. **\"Free\" and \"open source\" are magic words.** 2.5x more top
    performers mention these. They signal immediate value.

